  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LineDetectorController
    A class that implements LineDetectorController should use a single color sensor in order to detect lines.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DifferentialLineDetector
    Differential line detector that uses difference between old value and current value implements the line detector controller class
    GridRectangle
    A grid rectangle defined by 2 points in the grid coordinate system.
    LauncherControl
    Main class for methods that control the launcher
    LightLocalizer
    localises the robot using colour sensors to detect lines arranged in a grid in order to localise angle and position.
    Main
    The running point of the entire project.
    ModifiedLightLocalizer
    localises the robot using colour sensors to detect lines arranged in a grid in order to localise angle and position.
    Navigation
    Contains all the general navigation related methods.
    ObjectAvoidance
    The class concerning everything to use to avoid objects.
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) position.
    PDifferentialLineDetector
    A line detector that detects lines using a difference in the light levels proportional to their average values.
    PlainNavigation
    A simple navigation implementation.
    ProportionalLineDetector
    A simple line detector that detects lines based on a threshold proportional to its initial value.
    ReLocalizeNavigation
    A navigator that can corrects its heading and position.
    Resources
    Contains all of the constants and many of the variables shared by multiple classes, as well as containing all the resources imported over wifi.
    Resources.IntPoint
    Represents an integer value coordinate point on the competition map grid.
    Resources.Point
    Represents a coordinate point on the competition map grid.
    Resources.Region
    Represents a region on the competition map grid, delimited by its lower-left and upper-right corners (inclusive).
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    Uses an ultrasonic sensor to localise the robot.
    WaggleNavigation
    A navigator that actively corrects its heading and position.
